He's a beekeeper (those are beehives behind him) and I feel like beekeeping goes great with having a wilder, English-style garden. Beekeepers around my town also tend to have lots of greenery around their houses even if they are in the more urban inner city parts.

I have zero idea who Elizabeth Holmes is, but prison for white-collar crime has to be one of the most retarded concepts ever. Prison should be a way to lock dangerous and violent low IQ criminals away from society. What is she going to do, scam someone with three cups and a ball?

Obviously I subscribe to the usual rightwing orthodoxy that prisons are dubious at best and outside of forced labor, physical punishment is preferable for most cases, but even on a really normie level what is keeping some random failed CEO girl in prison supposed to even achieve?

And in fields like "biotech" obviously 99% of everything is a straightforward scam anyways, you're playing shitcoins with biology. She's basically getting punished for losing a 4D chess game while some of the worst, who have done far worse, walk free. Drumpft should pardon her.

Seize their assets, maybe light whooping, if they have a real talent appoint them somewhere productive, if not just ban them from ever doing anything related to finance or whatever scam field they are in

Feels like a lot of people would be happier if they had an old school analog clock on the wall. Waking up and seeing the dial with the hour hand pointing at 6 in the morning cheers you up. Seeing it on a phone screen is depressing. Ideally like a grandfather clock with a pendulum
